|Bust of the Marquise de Gueidan
|[[Gardenne]]
|align="center"|1903
|The last Marquise de Gueidan was a major benefactor of Gardenne and a bust was executed by Carli and erected in the Marquise's honour. The statue is known by the citizens of Gardenne as "La Bonne Personne".
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etoilesaintmichel.cef.fr/gardanne-021.htm
|title=Marquise de Gueidan|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ville-gardanne.fr/L-office-de-Tourisme-de-Gardanne
|title=Marquise de Gueidan 2|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref>
|-
|Caisse d'Épargne
|[[Marseille]]
|align="center"|1904
|The Groupe Caisse d'Épargne is a [[France|French]] semi-[[cooperative]] [[bank|banking group]], founded in 1818, with around 4700 [[Branch (banking)|branches]] in the country.  This Marseille Caisse d'Épargne building was inaugurated in July 1904.  The architect was Albert Tournaire and Carli's sculpture is positioned on one corner of the building. It is entitled "La Prévoyance dans ses fonctions" and in Carli's composition the bank are represented by a female figure holding up a "savings book" and surrounded by workers, farmers and pensioners, some of the groups to whom the cooperative would offer support and protection. A blacksmith offers up money to the safe-keeping of the bank and the pensioners are a reminder of a peaceful retirement which savings can ensure.  
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.petit-patrimoine.com/fiche-petit-patrimoine.php?id_pp=13206_2
|title=La Prévoyance dans ses fonctions|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref>
[[File:Carli-épargne.jpg|thumb|centre|250px]]
|-
|Fontaine d'Amphitrite
|Marseille.  Place Joseph Étienne
|align="center"|1904
|In 1904 the daughter of the shipowner Joseph Étienne commissioned this fountain in his memory. A plaque on the fountain records the names of some of Étienne's ships- "le Cèdre", "le Clarisse Louise", "le Goéland" and the " le Nicolas Étienne Jeune".  	
