|Monument to [[Victor Leydet]]
|[[Aix-en-Provence]]
|align="center"|1910
|Shown at the 1910 Salon des Artistes Français.  Originally a pedestal supported a bronze bust of Leydet with an allegory for Aix at his feet. The monument was inaugurated in December 1910. Sadly the bronze was taken and melted down by the occupying Germans in 1943 but later a smaller plaster bust, which had decorated Leydet's tomb in the local cemetery, replaced the bronze.
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ruesdaix.ag13.pagesperso-orange.fr/html/LEYDET.html
|title=Leydet 3|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>
